<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-194-136 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 611 227</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  March 27 1991 n155 p17(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM laptop makes a discreet entrance. (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Laptop ComputersProduct IntroductionMarket EntryPortable Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM laptop makes a discreet entrance IBM has quietly launched its laptop PC,a 386SX machine costing 3,495 pounds, although it will not ship for severalweeksandM;According to sources close to IBM, the official launch of the 7.7lb laptopwas scheduled for release yesterday (26 March).andP;  But dealers do not expectthe machine to ship until the middle of May.andM;The laptop weighs 7.7lbs and comprises a 2 1/2-inch 60Mb hard disk drive, a20MHz 386SX processor and a sidelit mono VGA LCD screen.andP;  The screen offers32 shades of grey with a resolution of 640x480.andP;  The machine comes with 2MbRAM as standard, although this is expandable to 18Mb on the system board.andM;IBM has signed a deal with a Salt Lake City company called Axonix which willoffer the LapStation, a cable-connected expansion unit which plugs the laptopinto a desktop PC.andP;  Axonix has already produced such units for Toshiba.andM;An IBM spokesman said that it would be sold through &quot;all authorised IBMdealers&quot;.andP;  However, distribution company Northamber, catalogue company ActionComputer Suppliers and high street retail Dixons say they have few detailsabout shipping dates.andP;  &quot;It has been announced to us, but we do not know howlong it would take if you ordered it,&quot; said Dixons.andP;  Action sales andmarketing director Duncan Wilks was told by IBM to expect deliveries at theend of April.andO;</TEXT></DOC>